trans-unit.source: A file's size is modified only if the request specifies a value for the <parameterReference>x-ms-content-length</parameterReference> header.
trans-unit.target: A file's size is modified only if the request specifies a value for the <parameterReference>x-ms-content-length</parameterReference> header.

trans-unit.source: If a request sets only <parameterReference>x-ms-content-length</parameterReference>, and no other properties, then none of the file’s other properties are modified.
trans-unit.target: If a request sets only <parameterReference>x-ms-content-length</parameterReference>, and no other properties, then none of the file’s other properties are modified.

trans-unit.source: If any one or more of the following properties is set in the request, then all of these properties are set together.
trans-unit.target: If any one or more of the following properties is set in the request, then all of these properties are set together.

trans-unit.source: If a value is not provided for a given property when at least one of the properties listed below is set, then that property will be cleared for the file.

trans-unit.source: The file properties listed above are discrete from the file system properties available to SMB clients.
